<item>
            <title>[JXR-96] [PATCH] JXR Comment handling has several shortcomings</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JXR-96</link>
                <project id="12317527" key="JXR">Maven JXR (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I have identified the following issues:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;a // comment does not properly mask a subsequent /* on the same line.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;explicitly tries not to terminate comments if */ is embedded in a string, but compilers don&apos;t behave this way.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;does not handle /*&lt;b&gt;/ construct properly: recognized as javadoc but not terminated, while it is better interpreted as /&lt;/b&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;empty&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;*/.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;


&lt;p&gt;I have addressed these issues + &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JXR-58&quot; title=&quot;Syntax highlighting broken for inline comments&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;JXR-58&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;JXR-58&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; by reworking the comment handling code.  Formerly the filters were applied &lt;/p&gt;
{ multiline, inline }
&lt;p&gt;; my version of the code uses &lt;/p&gt;
{ ongoing-multiline, inline, begin-multiline }
&lt;p&gt; specifically to address the first of the issues noted above.  I was unable to find any exhaustive tests for this code; please guide me if there is any further testing I can provide.  I have collapsed the duplicate code in these regions as much as possible, and since this project is on maven-parent v21 I believe I was justified in replacing the StringBuffers in affected areas with StringBuilders (obviously the whole file might benefit minutely from this treatment).&lt;/p&gt;</description>
